label: Access Device
definition: product intended for medical use to gain access to the body, such as cannula, tube, catheter or drainage

definition: application of medical access device, such as cannula, tube, catheter or drainage

label: Administrative Case
definition: administrative artifact for billing according to national healthcare billing guidelines, e.g. Swiss Diagnosis Related Groups, and local settings

label: Administrative Sex
definition: the sex of the individual used for administrative purposes

label: Adverse Event
definition: results from an intervention that caused unintentional harm

label: Adverse Event consequences
definition: consequences of the concept

label: Adverse Event outcome
definition: result or effect of an action, situation, or event of the concept

label: Age
definition: time elapsed since birth of the individual

label: Allergen
definition: any substance, product or physical force producing immediate hypersensitivity

label: Allergy
definition: risk of harmful or undesirable, physiological response which is unique to an individual and associated with exposure to an allergen

label: Allergy Episode
definition: manifestation of an allergic reaction following an exposure to an allergen

label: Antimicrobial Susceptibility Lab Test
definition: specific lab test performed on an isolate against a chemical agent for determining antimicrobial susceptibility

label: Antimicrobial Susceptibility Lab Test Event
definition: occurrence in which one or multiple laboratory tests are performed on an isolate at a given time for determining antimicrobial susceptibility

label: Antimicrobial Susceptibility Result
definition: result of a antimicrobial susceptibility lab analysis

label: Assay
definition: a process with the objective to produce information about a sample by examining it

label: Assessment
definition: assessment scale, classification, staging or scoring system

label: Assessment Component
definition: component of an assessment

label: Assessment Event
definition: evaluation at a given time, which takes into account a predefined scale, classification, staging or scoring system

label: Assessment Result
definition: outcome of an assessment

definition: discharge diagnosis used for the billing system (e.g. for building the Diagnosis Related Groups) according to guidelines of the national authority (e.g. Swiss Federal Office of Public Health), e.g. K35.3 acute appendicitis with localized peritonitis

label: Billed Diagnosis rank
definition: specifies the level of the concept

label: Billed Procedure
definition: procedure, coded for billing (e.g. for building the Diagnosis Related Groups) according to guidelines of the national authority (e.g. Swiss Federal Office of Public Health), e.g. Z57.34 open biopsy of the urinary bladder

label: Billed Procedure rank
definition: specifies the level of the concept

label: Biobanksample
definition: biosample stored in a biobank

label: Birth
definition: the event of being born

label: Birth Date
definition: the date and time of birth of the individual

label: Blood Pressure
definition: blood pressure of the individual

label: Blood Pressure Measurement
definition: measurement process of a blood pressure on an individual

label: Body Height
definition: height of the individual

label: Body Height Measurement
definition: measurement of the height of the individual

label: Body Mass Index
definition: body weight in kilograms divided by the square of the body height in meters

label: Body Position
definition: position of the body during a certain time interval, examination or therapy

label: Body Site
definition: any anatomical structure, any nonspecific and anatomical site, as well as morphologic abnormalities

label: Body Surface Area
definition: two dimensional measure of the outer layer of the body

label: Body Surface Area calculation method
definition: formula or method for calculating the concept

label: Body Temperature
definition: body temperature of the individual

label: Body Temperature Measurement
definition: measurement of the body temperature of the individual

label: Body Weight
definition: weight of the individual

label: Body Weight Measurement
definition: measurement of the weight of the individual

label: Cardiac Index
definition: cardiac output in relation to the body surface area (BSA)

label: Cardiac Output
definition: volume of blood passing through the heart per unit of time

label: Cardiac Output Measurement
definition: measurement of the cardiac output of the individual

label: Care Handling
definition: describes the relationship between the individual and care provider institute

label: Chromosomal Location
definition: chromosome locus defined as cytoband intervals

label: Chromosome
definition: thread-like structure composed of tightly coiled DNA and histones or circular DNA (mitochondrial DNA). These structures act as carriers of genetic information

label: Circumference
definition: circumference of a body site

label: Circumference Measurement
definition: measurement of the circumference measure of a body site

label: Civil Status
definition: the civil status indicates the familial and social situation of the individual

label: Code
definition: symbols and/or expressions defined in a coding system

label: Comparator
definition: qualifier describing whether the value is the precise one or not

label: Consent
definition: information on the individuals permission to make health related data and collected samples available for research purposes

label: Copy Number Variation
definition: structural genomic variant characterized by relative changes in the number of copies of a specific genomic segment compared to a reference sequence

label: Country
definition: distinct part of the world, such as a state, nation, or other political entity, often but not necessarily a sovereign state

label: Data Determination
definition: describes how the data was determined, e.g. measured, calculated

label: Data File
definition: electronic resource of information, which can be stored, accessed and transferred as a single unit

label: Data File encoding
definition: encoding of the concept

label: Data Processing
definition: a process that produces output data from input data

label: Data Provider
definition: provider of data of interest

label: Data Provider category
definition: category associated to the concept

label: Data Release
definition: Metadata about the release of the data

label: Death
definition: cessation of all vital bodily functions

label: Death Date
definition: the date and time of death of the individual

label: Department
definition: dedicated division of an organization

label: Deprecated
definition: Deprecated classes of SPHN that existed in the previous version

label: Diagnosis
definition: determination of the presence of a disease, condition, or injury from expressed signs and symptoms and assessments such as physical examination, laboratory test, or the like

label: Drug
definition: any substance with the intent to prevent, diagnose, treat, or relieve symptoms of a disease or abnormal condition

label: Drug Administration Event
definition: single event at which a drug was administered to the patient; this could be a single time point in case of a pill/cream or a duration in case of a single infusion pack or a single patch; one or many drug administration events are initiated by a drug prescription depending on the frequency stated in the prescription

label: Drug Article
definition: general details identifying a medication on the level of its commercial article

label: Drug Prescription
definition: plan that defines at which frequency a drug should be administered to a patient with a given quantity; at every frequency time point a drug administration event should occur

label: Electrocardiogram
definition: output of an electrocardiographic procedure

label: Electrocardiographic Procedure
definition: electrographic procedure on the heart which results in a graph of voltage versus time visualizing the electrical activity of the heart muscle using electrodes placed on the skin

label: Excluded Disorder
definition: determination of the absence of a disease

label: Exposure
definition: contact between a physical, biological, or chemical agent and an individual

label: Fluid Balance
definition: difference between fluid input and output during a specified time interval

label: Fluid Input Output
definition: gain or loss of fluid that impacts the fluid balance

label: Follow Up
definition: procedure for following up on the patient status

label: Gene
definition: fundamental unit of heredity that contains necessary elements to encode for a transcript

label: Gene Panel
definition: collection of genes that have been grouped for testing

label: Genetic Variation
definition: a genetic variation occurring at a defined position

label: Genomic Deletion
definition: genetic variant involving the deletion of a specific location in a DNA sequence

label: Genomic Insertion
definition: genetic variant involving the addition of a DNA sequence in a specific location

label: Genomic Position
definition: genomic position with respect to a reference

label: Genomic Position coordinate convention
definition: convention used for the interpretation of coordinates used in the concept

label: Gestational Age At Birth
definition: gestational age of a child at birth

label: Hash
definition: irreversible unique number computed on an information entity used to check its validity and integrity

label: Hash algorithm
definition: algorithm applied to the concept

label: Healthcare Encounter
definition: an interaction between an individual and a specific unit or service of a healthcare provider institute, e.g. emergency, intensive care unit, for the purpose of providing healthcare service(s) or assessing the health status of an individual

label: Healthcare Primary Information System
definition: primary source system of the healthcare data

label: Heart Rate
definition: frequency of the heart beats, i.e. the number of time a heart beats per unit of time

label: Heart Rate Measurement
definition: measurement of the heart rate of the individual

label: Home Address
definition: permanent place of residence of an individual

label: Imaging Procedure
definition: imaging procedure used for examination of a body site or function

label: Implant
definition: implanted medical device, includes, e.g., heart valve prostheses or joint prostheses

label: Implant Presence
definition: presence of an implanted medical device

label: Inhaled Oxygen Concentration
definition: fraction of inspired oxygen (FiO2) either calculated knowing the device used and the amount of oxygen administered or coming from the respiratory system settings

label: Insurance Status
definition: status of the patient's medical insurance

label: Insurance Status coverage type
definition: coverage type of the concept

label: Intent
definition: treatment or procedure purpose

label: Interpretation
definition: process of making sense of an outcome to derive meaningful conclusions

label: Isolate
definition: a specific individual microbe and its clone separated on a single occasion from a sample taken from a host or culture system

label: Lab Analyzer
definition: laboratory analyzer used to assess medical laboratory samples

label: Lab Result
definition: outcome, value, or information which gives insight about a laboratory test

label: Lab Test
definition: specific laboratory test performed to analyze a sample with a given equipment and leading to specific results

label: Lab Test Event
definition: occurrence in which one or multiple laboratory tests are performed on a biological specimen at a given time

label: Laterality
definition: localization with respect to the side of the body

label: Library Preparation
definition: process which results in the creation of a library from fragments of DNA

label: Location
definition: physical location or medical division taking care of the individual

label: Measurement
definition: process of quantitatively defining the value or magnitude of an attribute or characteristic in comparison to a defined standard

label: Medical Device
definition: product intended for medical use when the main effect is not achieved by a medicinal product; medical devices include, but are not limited to, implants, instruments, devices, in vitro diagnostics

label: Medical Procedure
definition: invasive or non-invasive intervention performed for, with or on behalf of an individual whose purpose is to assess, improve, maintain, promote or modify health, functioning or health conditions

label: Microbiology Biomolecule Presence Lab Test
definition: specific lab test performed on an isolate for detecting the presence of a target biomolecule

label: Microbiology Biomolecule Presence Lab Test Event
definition: occurrence in which one or multiple laboratory tests are performed on an isolate at a given time to detect the presence of a biomolecule

label: Microbiology Biomolecule Presence Result
definition: result of microbiology biomolecule presence test for a specific isolate analyzed

label: Microbiology Microscopy Lab Test
definition: specific microbiology microscopy lab test performed on a sample

label: Microbiology Microscopy Lab Test Event
definition: occurrence in which one or multiple microbiology microscopy laboratory tests are performed on a sample at a given time

label: Microbiology Microscopy Result
definition: microscopy analysis results for a specific studied biosample in microbiology

label: Microbiology Microscopy Result cell morphology
definition: cell morphology associated to the concept

label: Microbiology Microscopy Result cell organization
definition: cell organization associated to the concept

label: Microorganism Identification Lab Test
definition: specific lab test performed on a sample for identifying microorganism(s)

label: Microorganism Identification Lab Test Event
definition: occurrence in which one or multiple laboratory tests are performed on a sample at a given time for identifying microorganism(s)

label: Microorganism Identification Result
definition: result of the microorganism identification lab test

label: Nationality
definition: nationality of the individual

label: Nursing Diagnosis
definition: clinical judgment concerning a human response to health conditions/life processes, or a vulnerability for that response, by an individual, family, group or community; a nursing diagnosis provides the basis for selection of nursing interventions to achieve outcomes for which the nurse has accountability

label: Nutrition Intake
definition: intake of nutritious substance and/or the respective amount of energy consumed

label: Oncology Diagnosis
definition: determination of the presence of an oncological disease, from expressed signs and symptoms and assessments such as biopsy, tumor marker test, imaging, or the like

label: Oncology Surgery
definition: invasive intervention performed for, with or on behalf of an individual whose purpose is to improve, maintain or promote health, or functioning conditions in the context of an oncological disease, by the means of partial or complete exeresis of a solid tumor lesion that is the organic substrate of this disease

label: Organ Support
definition: type and time period when patient was supported by organ support procedures

label: Organism
definition: living system capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance. An organism may be unicellular or multicellular

label: Oxygen Saturation
definition: fraction of oxygen present in the blood

label: Oxygen Saturation Measurement
definition: measurement of the oxygen saturation of the individual

label: Performer
definition: person who carried out the action

label: Pharmaceutical Dose Form
definition: physical manifestation of a product that contains the active ingredient(s) and/or inactive ingredient(s) that are intended to be delivered to the patient

label: Physiologic State
definition: physiologic state of the individual, e.g. resting, exercise

label: Problem Condition
definition: clinical condition, problem, diagnosis, or other event, situation, issue, or clinical concept that has risen to a level of concern

label: Protein
definition: molecule composed by one or more chains of amino acids

label: Quality Control Metric
definition: report of the quality control review that was made of factors involved in a procedure

label: Quantity
definition: an amount or a number of something

label: Radiotherapy Procedure
definition: given radiotherapy procedure during oncological treatment

label: Reference Interpretation
definition: process of making sense of a quantitative result to derive meaningful conclusions in comparison to a reference

label: Reference Interpretation Result
definition: outcome of the interpretation of a reference range or value

label: Reference Range
definition: interval of values that is deemed normal for a physiologic measurement in healthy individuals

label: Reference Sequence
definition: reference construct used for comparison purposes

label: Reference Value
definition: numeric data point serving as reference for comparison and interpretation

label: Respiratory Rate
definition: frequency at which the breathing occurs

label: Respiratory Rate Measurement
definition: measurement of the frequency at which the breathing occurs

label: Result
definition: outcome, value, or information which gives insight about something

label: Resuscitation Directive
definition: decision about the extent of resuscitation interventions appropriate for a specific individual

label: SPHN Concept
definition: SPHN Concepts defined by the SPHN dataset

label: Sample
definition: any material sample for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes

label: Sample Processing
definition: a process that prepares a sample for a subsequent process

label: Sample fixation type
definition: fixation or stabilization type

label: Sample primary container
definition: type of primary container of the concept

label: Semantic Mapping
definition: process of transforming data elements to a code

label: Semantic Mapping purpose
definition: objective of the concept

label: Sequencing Analysis
definition: analysis of the output of a nucleic acid sequencing assay

label: Sequencing Assay
definition: an assay that exploits a sequencer as the instrument to generate results

label: Sequencing Instrument
definition: A sequencing instrument that is used in a sequencing assay

label: Sequencing Run
definition: the valid and completed operation of a high-throughput sequencing instrument associated with a sequencing assay

label: Single Nucleotide Variation
definition: single nucleotide change in a DNA sequence at a specific location

label: Software
definition: Set of procedures and instructions in a data processing system

label: Source Data
definition: raw data that has not been processed for meaningful use

label: Source System
definition: electronic system the data has been retrieved from

label: Source System category
definition: category associated to the concept

label: Source System purpose
definition: objective of the concept

label: Standard Operating Procedure
definition: step-by-step instructions for carrying out routine operations imposed by the organization

label: Subject Pseudo Identifier
definition: a coded unique identifier assigned by a data provider for a specific project to conceal the identity of an individual

label: Substance
definition: any matter of defined composition that has discrete existence, whose origin may be biological, mineral or chemical

label: Swiss Socio Economic Position
definition: characterization or classification of the Swiss position in a neighbourhood of an individual that takes into account income, education, occupation, and housing conditions

label: Terminology
definition: Terminology class for grouping external resources used in the SPHN project

label: Therapeutic Area
definition: professional health care specialization

label: Therapeutic Area specialty name
definition: name of professional health care specialization

label: Time Pattern
definition: type of time period during which a treatment was given or an assessment was performed; this can be single time points or a continuous event

label: Time Series Data File
definition: electronic resource that contains all the results related to a measurement as time series

label: Tobacco Exposure
definition: episode of exposure of an individual to tobacco in various forms

label: Transcript
definition: RNA molecules that are made from a DNA template

definition: transplanted organ or tissue from self or donor, including, e.g., kidney graft or bone marrow fluid

label: Transplant Presence
definition: presence of a transplanted organ or tissue such as, e.g., a kidney graft

definition: grading system used to assess the differentiation of the tumor cells based on histology

label: Tumor Grade Assessment Event
definition: evaluation of the tumor grade at a given time, which takes into account a predefined grading system

label: Tumor Grade Assessment Result
definition: outcome of a tumor grade assessment

label: Tumor Specimen
definition: tumor specimen, volume and fixation method used

label: Tumor Stage Assessment
definition: staging system used to assess the spread of the oncology disease

label: Tumor Stage Assessment Event
definition: evaluation of the tumor stage at a given time, which takes into account a predefined staging system

label: Tumor Stage Assessment Result
definition: outcome of a tumor stage assessment

label: Unit
definition: unit of measurement

label: Value Set
definition: List of value sets provided by SPHN

label: Variant Descriptor
definition: human-readable description of the variant

label: Variant Notation
definition: description of the variant using a specific nomenclature

label: Vital Status
definition: state or condition of being living or deceased
